## 5. Cross-app routing and ecosystem weaving already happening

### SuperIDE already behaves like an orchestration shell
The main SuperIDE surface already includes an app strip, grouped drawer, execution pipeline controls, workspace stack configuration, and a direct link from the file-safety policy to the SKNore console. In other words: the shell already understands that apps are part of one governed bench, not isolated tabs.

### SkyDex already routes into sovereign systems
SkyDex 4.6 can record suite intents and sync workspace context directly into SovereignVariables. It also stages bridge drafts into SkyeBlog, posts recalled blog content into SkyeChat, and sends the same content into SkyeMail. So the behavior you want — “all my apps talking to one another” — is already partially implemented in live surfaces.

### SovereignVariables already participates in cross-stream routing
SovereignVariables has queued-intake auto-import, app-aware auth headers, suite-intent recording, and direct push functions for SkyeChat and SkyeMail. This means it is already a sovereign workflow node, not just a passive secret editor.

### SkyeDocxPro and SkyeBlog already publish into the ecosystem
SkyeDocxPro can stage content into SkyeBlog, publish to SkyeChat, send to SkyeMail, and mirror into SkyeDrive. SkyeBlog can receive bridge drafts, publish to SkyeChat, and deliver to SkyeMail while recording suite intents. These are the exact interaction patterns the sovereign primitives layer should standardize and harden.

